notes: Conditional logic via Python control flow

components.name: Extract User Content
components.description: Reads the CSV file containing usergenerated content and emits metadata such as total item count and file path via XCom.

connections.purpose: Read CSV file from local disk

components.name: Evaluate Toxicity
components.description: Computes a toxicity score for the extracted content and decides which downstream branch to follow based on a 0.7 threshold.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after successful extraction of user content.

components.name: Remove and Flag Toxic Content
components.description: Deletes content identified as toxic and flags the associated user accounts for review.

upstream_policy.description: Executed only when toxicity_check routes to this branch (toxicity > 0.7).

connections.purpose: Interact with platform content management system to delete content and flag users

components.name: Publish Safe Content
components.description: Publishes content deemed nontoxic to the platform for user visibility.

upstream_policy.description: Executed only when toxicity_check routes to this branch (toxicity  0.7).

connections.purpose: Send safe content to the platform publishing service

components.name: Create Audit Log
components.description: Aggregates outcomes from both removal/flagging and publishing branches and writes a consolidated audit log entry.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after both branch paths have completed, regardless of which branch was taken.

batch_window.description: Batch window parameter name (e.g., ds, execution_date)

partitioning.description: Data partitioning strategy (e.g., daily, hourly, monthly)

depends_on_past.description: Whether execution depends on previous run success

csv_file_path.description: Path to the CSV file containing usergenerated content
csv_file_path.constraints: must be a readable file path

toxicity_threshold.description: Score threshold that determines branching (high toxicity > threshold)

provide_context.description: Enable XCom context passing from both upstream branches

sources: Usergenerated content CSV file located at /data/user_content.csv
sinks: Removal confirmation sent to the Platform Content Management System
Publication confirmation sent to the Platform Publishing System
Consolidated audit log entry written to the Audit Logging System
Failure alert emails sent via the Email Notification Service
